query.result:
97 And before, near the end of these words,
98 “Let them hope in you” from above us was heard;
99 to which responded all the dances.

109 I placed them there in the song and in the wheel;
110 and my lady held the appearance among them,
111 just like a silent and motionless bride.

118 As is the one who watches and argues 119 to see the sun eclipsed a little, 120 who, in order to see, becomes not seeing;
121 such did I make myself at that last fire 122 while it was said: “Why do you dazzle 123 to see a thing that does not have place here?
124 In earth is earth my body, and it will be 125 so with the others, that our number 126 with the eternal purpose will be matched.”

127 With the two robes in the blessed cloister
128 are the two lights alone that ascended;
129 and this you will bring into your world.
